						"title": null,
						"subtitle": null,
						"copy": "<div style= \"text-align:center; font-size: 28px; font-weight: bold; line-height:125%\" >Shielding the Future:<br>Middle East Cyber Threat Landscape Report\n </div><br>\n<div style= \"text-align:center; font-size: 20px; color:rgb(0, 86, 220);font-weight: normal; line-height:125%\" >\nDownload the full report for complete details. \n </div><br>\n\n![EMEA survey report ME report](//cf-assets.www.cloudflare.com/slt3lc6tev37/6zVVNN3xVsGUmr95ZiePLj/9861879247ee118d7016a02a041ad259/EMEA-survey-report-ME-report.png)\n\nIn this 2024 Cloudflare study, we set out to build a better understanding of the threat landscape facing Chief Information Security Officers (CISOs) and their teams across the Middle East; interviewing 900 cybersecurity professionals from 3 markets across the region.\n\nThe report includes new findings on security preparedness and outcomes, revealing how organizations are coping with rising volumes of cybersecurity incidents, their levels of preparedness and the outcomes experienced. The results are both illuminating and alarming, with the survey revealing that across the region attacks are increasing, and yet not all organizations are sufficiently prepared.\n\nSome highlights from the report :\n- 53% of the respondents experienced at least one cybersecurity incident in the past 12 months.\n- Only 46% of organizations think they are highly prepared to address a cybersecurity incident.\n- 69% of respondents say they are challenged by the number of siloed tools and homegrown solutions for data protection, security, sovereignty, localization, residency, and privacy.\n\nAs we look to the future of our industry, we hope that this report will provide useful reading and inspiration for CISOs and cybersecurity teams in the region looking to achieve a better understanding of the cybersecurity risks at play, and how to achieve better outcomes for their organizations.\n\nDownload the full report for complete details or download the country-specific report where we drill down results pertinent to each country.\n",
